  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency health response in Badakhshan and Nooristan provinces</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to answer some of the needs of drought affected population in Nooristan and Badakhshan provinces, YHDO proposes an emergency health and nutrition response to 4 categories of drought-related effects: 1) general health problems 2) water-related disease 3) airborne and dust-related disease and 4) vector-borne disease. YHDO will also ensure the referral system to HF&#x2019;s managed by BPHS implementer for emergency cases encountered in project locations. In Nooristan, the 3 districts targeted are: Paroon, Noor Gram and Wama. In Badakhshan, the 5 districts targeted are: Yaftal-e-Sufla, Arghanjkhwa, Zebak, Teshkan and Keshem. YHDO will enable the following activities: 

 Establishment of 5 sub health centers in white areas of the 2 provinces 
 Enabling referral system through 8 ambulances (5 cars in white areas and 3 for existing BHCs supported)
 Support to 3 existing BHCs (2 in Badakhshan and 1 in Nooristan)
 Support to 4 existing CHCs (3 in Badakhshan and 1 in Nooristan) 
 Counselling on feeding best practices and establishment of breastfeeding corners in the health facilities (12)

The total beneficiaries reached by the project will be 16 443 individuals, as per target calculations details attached to the proposal. YHDO has been operating in Badakhshan since several years and currently implement HIV NFM project funded by UNDP in the province. YHDO also have extended network in Nooristan and smooth access to the 3 central districts targeted. In both provinces, the impacts of the drought have been observed and quantified, especially in the last months. The severity of the drought is expected to increase and cause further famine plus potential displacement in the districts affected. 

YHDO is able to deploy teams quickly, as soon as recruitment and procurement processes are completed. The organization has office and permanent team in Badakhshan province and will be provided a working and storage space in Nooristan MoPH office.</narrative>
  </description>
